      <hedline>
        <hl1>MADE TO MEASURE</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Ferriss ends her article not with the idea that women should be judged on their abilities and intellect, but rather that " very sexy, procreative, small-breasted women" should be featured in beer ads, on sitcoms and on Cosmopolitan's cover. She doesn't seek to change the rating system, she only wants to rate within it. I feel sorry for her. HELEN GRIFFIN</p>
        <p>Little Neck, L.I.</p>
      </block>
